summary: An email from a paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY inquiring about experience with '.anb' files (IBM Analyst Notebook files) found while de-duping files for 'Maxwell 3500 production'. The email seeks technical assistance to view these files, indicating they were part of evidence processing in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

events.title: Email inquiry about .anb files
events.description: A paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office SDNY sends an email seeking information about '.anb' files (IBM Analyst Notebook files) found during file de-duplication for 'Maxwell 3500 production'.

locations: 1 Saint Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: The email is dated September 17, 2021, from a paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
The specialist is working on 'de duping some files for Maxwell 3500 production', referencing Ghislaine Maxwell's case.

The inquiry concerns files with an '.anb' extension, identified as being created with IBM 'Analyst Notebook' software, suggesting the files may contain analytical or link-chart data relevant to the investigation.
The email indicates ongoing evidence processing and technical challenges in accessing certain file types in the Maxwell case.
